modules.description: This module defines core types and constants for numerical computations, including number types (float32, float64, complex32, complex64), index and slice representations for tensor operations, and device types (CPU, OpenCL, CUDA). It provides direct access to version information and bigarray kind values for memory-efficient data handling. Concrete use cases include configuring tensor operations, specifying array indices and ranges, and selecting computation devices in numerical libraries.

This module supports creating and customizing 2D/3D visualizations of numerical data, offering operations for statistical plots (e.g., histograms, Q-Q plots), geometric shapes (lines, bars), and advanced renderings like surface/mesh plots or heatmaps. It processes dense matrices (`dsmat`) and vectors to generate visualizations, with styling controls for colors, labels, and layouts, catering to data analysis, numerical simulations, and publication-quality graphics. Key workflows include iterative plot refinement through low-level graphical primitives and high-level automated visual summaries of datasets.
